Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Cut @Potatoes{12%ounce} into 1⁄2-inch-thick wedges. Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a large
drizzle of @Cooking Oil{}, @Salt{}, and @Pepper{}.

Roast on middle rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, zest and halve @Orange{1}. Squeeze juice from half the orange (whole orange for
4 servings) into a #small bowl{}.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @Coleslaw Mix{4%ounce}, 1 TBSP orange juice (2 TBSP for 4),
a pinch of zest, a drizzle of @Olive Oil{}, salt (we used 1⁄4 tsp), and pepper. Toss to
coat; set aside until ready to serve.

In a separate small bowl, combine @Mayonnaise{2%ounce}, half the @Jerk Sauce{2%ounce}, and
1 TBSP water (2 TBSP for 4).

In a second medium bowl, gently combine @Ground Beef{10%ounce}, remaining jerk sauce,
@Panko Breadcrumbs{¼%cup}, and a pinch of salt.

Form beef mixture into two patties (four patties for 4 servings), each slightly wider
than a burger bun.

Heat a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add patties and
cook to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Halve and toast @Brioche Buns{2}; spread a thin layer of spicy jerk mayo on cut sides.

Fill buns with patties and citrus slaw. Divide burgers and potato wedges between plates.
Serve with remaining spicy jerk mayo on the side for dipping.

> Ground Meat is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 160°.